java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible, AllowingPropertyChanges, PiptData, PiptSafelyAccessible
public class ETCSpectrumPlotPanel
extends javax.swing.JPanel
implements PiptData

This class provides a panel containing a plot for a spectrum. By default, the abscissa values are assumed to be wavelengths given in Angstrom, but no assumption is made concerning the ordinate.

Constructor Detail

ETCSpectrumPlotPanel

public ETCSpectrumPlotPanel(Grid spectrum,
                            java.lang.String title,
                            java.lang.String yLabel,
                            double[] xRange,
                            double[] yRange,
                            boolean xAutoscale,
                            boolean yAutoscale)
Creates the panel with the plot for the given spectrum and value ranges. If the xAutoscale and yAutoscale parameters are true, zero fluxes at the interval edges are ignored for the abscissa and the ordinate range of the binned ordinate values is used. In case null is specified for a range, it is obtained from the given spectrum.

Parameters:
spectrum - the spectrum to be plotted
title - the plot title
yLabel - the ordinate label
xRange - the abscissa range (may be null)
yRange - the ordinate range (may be null)
xAutoscale - states whether to ignore zero fluxes at the abscissa interval edges
yAutoscale - states whether to use the value range of the binned (rather than original) ordinate values
